1951;;Sunny Side of the Street;;American;;Richard Quine;;Frankie Laine, Audrey Long;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunny_Side_of_the_Street_(film);;Betty Holloway (Terry Moore) a receptionist at a major TV station hopes to secure a break for her singer boyfriend Ted Mason (Jerome Courtland), Betty enlists the aid of Laine. Mason's career really takes off when a team of TV writers discover that he's the childhood sweetheart of Gloria Pelly (Audrey Long), the daughter of an important sponsor.[2]